reviews.text: Quiet and clean restaurant that is not crowded in the evening. Dishes cater to local taste for western food.  Good food but meat was overcooked. Waiters are friendly and polite.   Good place if you want to meet up with friends for a quiet chat in the late afternoon. However, they do close shop quite early.
Nice environment but over-priced by around 20%
already pre-ordered lunch, the main course waiting takes 30min+,  the table setting is not comfort to sit, but the food tastes good!

Nice place to hangout, good food & good atmosphere. Love that it’s not crowded even on a Friday night and free parking provided. 

But the staffs could be friendlier, every-time when requesting something, he/she will start with “要咩？” ( what you want ?). =.=
Great food.

reviews.text: Most of the staffs are very nice, but some are impolite. Rooms are clean and we got everything we need. Overall nice and satisfied experience.
Had a wonderful stay.  Room housekeeping was excellent
Nice rooms good service. But lacking restaurant

Solid value for money. A beautifully executed reuse of the owner's former vacuum flask factory that incorporates numerous elements of it's former incarnation into the design. The hotel offers adequate space (large for its price point), good service, a very good coffee shop and convenient location for business in the Kowloon Bay area.

The overall of the hotel is pretty alright. The room is nice, in a good size. The staff can speak english pretty well. The only thing that’s not good about this hotel, is the location. It’s far from the transportation, especially the train.
